transcripts:
[MUSIC PLAYING]

Were gonna cook a rutabaga. so I'm going to use a chef knife which is sharp and has a really hard base here that goes all the way through this vegetable. cut one side off so you can cut it without rolling around. We're gonna cut this one straight in half. Again sharp knife in, hand firmly on the blade, slicing forward, and then back and forth. I'm going to switch knives to the five inch santoku knife in order to peel it. take the santoku in your hand and then just start gliding with the small tip forward and down along the edge. I'm going to move back to the chef knife in order to dice these vegetables. Just do a rough cut on it. Here you have a peeled and diced rutabaga ready for roasting
